  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a literature-review of published hemolysis correlations and benchmark datasets. The narrative presents the literature survey as a comprehensive and complementary evidence source, obscuring the fact that no physical experiments were performed against the model predictions. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels fall below required levels across the board. Decision: Accepted (inference chain is structurally broken by method mismatch).",
